The paper discusses the potential application of quantum computing to artificial intelligence, which suggests that it would likely fall under the cs.AI sub-category. Additionally, the paper covers basic principles of quantum computing, which could place it in the cs.ET (emerging technologies) sub-category. The paper also discusses quantum algorithms, which could place it in the cs.CC (computational complexity) sub-category. The use of quantum computing for search and pattern matching could place it in the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses research guidelines, which could place it in the cs.PL (programming languages) sub-category.
